# Slidev Cursor Rules

## Overview
Slidev is a slides maker and presenter designed for developers. It uses Markdown with Vue.js components and special syntax for creating interactive presentations.

## File Structure
- Main presentation file: `slides.md`
- Components: `./components/` directory
- External snippets: `./snippets/` directory
- Imported slides: `./pages/` directory

## Frontmatter Syntax
Each slide starts with YAML frontmatter between `---` delimiters:

```yaml
---
theme: seriph                    # Theme name
background: https://cover.sli.dev # Background image
title: Welcome to Slidev         # Slide title
info: |                          # Multi-line info
  ## Slidev Starter Template
  Presentation slides for developers.
class: text-center               # CSS classes for the slide
drawings:                        # Drawing settings
  persist: false
transition: slide-left           # Slide transition
mdc: true                        # Enable MDC syntax
level: 2                         # Heading level for TOC
layout: two-cols                 # Layout type
layoutClass: gap-16              # Layout CSS classes
image: https://cover.sli.dev     # Image for image layouts
src: ./pages/imported-slides.md  # Import external slide file
hide: false                      # Hide slide from TOC
---
```

## Slide Separators
Use `---` to separate slides:
```markdown
# Slide 1 content

---

# Slide 2 content
```

## Layouts
Slidev provides several built-in layouts:

### Default Layout
```markdown
# Regular slide content
```

### Two Columns
```markdown
---
layout: two-cols
layoutClass: gap-16
---

# Left column content

::right::

# Right column content
```

### Image Right
```markdown
---
layout: image-right
image: https://example.com/image.jpg
---

# Content with image on the right
```

### Center Layout
```markdown
---
layout: center
class: text-center
---

# Centered content
```

## Vue Directives

### Click Animations
```html
<div v-click>Content that appears on click</div>
<div v-click="2">Content that appears on second click</div>
<div v-after>Content that appears after previous element</div>
```

### Motion Animations
```html
<div
  v-motion
  :initial="{ x: -80, opacity: 0 }"
  :enter="{ x: 0, opacity: 1 }"
  :click-3="{ x: 80 }"
  :leave="{ x: 1000 }"
>
  Animated content
</div>
```

### Marking Elements
```html
<span v-mark.red="3">Red highlight on click 3</span>
<span v-mark.circle.orange="4">Orange circle on click 4</span>
<span v-mark.underline.orange>Inline underline</span>
```

### Draggable Elements
```html
<img v-drag="'square'" src="image.jpg">
<v-drag pos="x,y,width,height,rotation">
  <div>Draggable content</div>
</v-drag>
<v-drag-arrow pos="x1,y1,x2,y2" two-way />
```

## Code Blocks

### Basic Code Highlighting
```markdown
```ts
const example = "TypeScript code"
```
```

### Line Highlighting
```markdown
```ts {1|3|5-7}
// Lines 1, 3, and 5-7 will be highlighted
const example = "highlighted"
```
```

### Monaco Editor
```markdown
```ts {monaco}
// Editable code block
const editable = "edit me"
```
```

### Monaco Runner
```markdown
```ts {monaco-run}
// Executable code block
console.log("runs in browser")
```
```

### TwoSlash Support
```markdown
```ts {all|4|6|6-7|9|all} twoslash
// TypeScript with hover information
import { computed, ref } from 'vue'
```
```

### Magic Move (Code Transitions)
```markdown
````md magic-move {lines: true}
```ts {*|2|*}
// Step 1
```

```ts {*|1-2|3-4|3-4,8}
// Step 2
```
````
```

## Built-in Components

### Table of Contents
```html
<Toc minDepth="1" maxDepth="2" />
```

### Tweet Embed
```html
<Tweet id="1390115482657726468" scale="0.65" />
```

### YouTube Embed
```html
<Youtube id="video-id" />
```

### Arrows
```html
<arrow v-click="[4, 5]" x1="350" y1="310" x2="195" y2="342" color="#953" width="2" arrowSize="1" />
```

### Powered By
```html
<PoweredBySlidev mt-10 />
```

## External Code Inclusion
```markdown
<<< @/snippets/external.ts#snippet
```

## Diagrams

### Mermaid Diagrams
```markdown
```mermaid {scale: 0.5, alt: 'Description'}
sequenceDiagram
    Alice->John: Hello John, how are you?
```
```

### PlantUML Diagrams
```markdown
```plantuml {scale: 0.7}
@startuml
package "Some Group" {
  HTTP - [First Component]
}
@enduml
```
```

## LaTeX Support

### Inline Math
```markdown
Inline $\sqrt{3x-1}+(1+x)^2$
```

### Block Math with Animations
```markdown
$$ {1|3|all}
\begin{aligned}
\nabla \cdot \vec{E} &= \frac{\rho}{\varepsilon_0}
\end{aligned}
$$
```

## CSS and Styling

### Slide-scoped Styles
```html
<style>
h1 {
  background-color: #2B90B6;
  background-image: linear-gradient(45deg, #4EC5D4 10%, #146b8c 20%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}
</style>
```

### UnoCSS Classes
```html
<div grid="~ cols-2 gap-4" m="t-4">
  <div>Left column</div>
  <div>Right column</div>
</div>
```

### Custom Classes
```html
<div class="abs-br m-6 text-xl">
  <button class="slidev-icon-btn">
    <carbon:edit />
  </button>
</div>
```

## Vue Script Setup
```html
<script setup lang="ts">
const final = {
  x: 0,
  y: 0,
  rotate: 0,
  scale: 1,
  transition: {
    type: 'spring',
    damping: 10,
    stiffness: 20,
    mass: 2
  }
}
</script>
```

## Event Handling
```html
<div @click="$slidev.nav.next" class="mt-12 py-1" hover:bg="white op-10">
  Press Space for next page <carbon:arrow-right />
</div>

<button @click="$slidev.nav.openInEditor()" title="Open in Editor">
  <carbon:edit />
</button>
```

## Icons
Use Carbon icons with the `carbon:` prefix:
```html
<carbon:arrow-right />
<carbon:edit />
<carbon:logo-github />
```

## Notes
Add presenter notes using HTML comments at the end of slides:
```html
<!--
Presenter note with **bold**, *italic*, and ~~striked~~ text.

[click] This will be highlighted after the first click
[click:3] Last click (skip two clicks)
-->
```

## Keyboard Shortcuts Reference
- `right` / `space`: next animation or slide
- `left` / `shift+space`: previous animation or slide
- `up`: previous slide
- `down`: next slide

## Best Practices

1. **Slide Structure**: Always use `---` to separate slides
2. **Frontmatter**: Keep frontmatter concise and relevant
3. **Animations**: Use `v-click` sparingly for better flow
4. **Code**: Use appropriate language tags and line highlighting
5. **Components**: Leverage built-in components for common functionality
6. **Styling**: Use UnoCSS classes for consistent styling
7. **Notes**: Add presenter notes for better presentation delivery
8. **Accessibility**: Include alt text for images and proper heading structure

## Common Patterns

### Interactive Elements
```html
<div v-click>
  <div v-click="2">
    <span v-mark.red="3">Highlighted text</span>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Grid Layouts
```html
<div grid="~ cols-2 gap-4" m="t-4">
  <div>Content 1</div>
  <div>Content 2</div>
</div>
```

### Code with Arrows
```ts
// Code block
const example = "code"
```
<arrow v-click="[1, 2]" x1="100" y1="100" x2="200" y2="200" color="#953" width="2" />

### Imported Slides
```markdown
---
src: ./pages/imported-slides.md
hide: false
---
```

## Theme Configuration
Themes can be configured in frontmatter:
```yaml
---
theme: seriph
themeConfig:
  primary: '#42b883'
  secondary: '#35495e'
---
```

## Export Options
Slidev can export to:
- PDF: `slidev export`
- PNG: `slidev export --format png`
- PPTX: `slidev export --format pptx`
- SPA: `slidev build` 